  "title": "Question on the page \"Create a calendar widget\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[Create a calendar widget](__LOCATION__)\".\r\n\r\nI am struggling to get this to work when my date is within an array. My data is coming from craft cms and therefore outputs like so;\r\n\r\n\"eventDate\": {\r\n        \"localeDate\": \"5/12/2017\",\r\n        \"localeTime\": \"2:30 PM\",\r\n        \"nice\": \"May 12, 2017, 2:30:00 PM\",\r\n        \"mysql\": \"2017-05-12 14:30:00\",\r\n        \"cookie\": \"Friday, 12-May-2017 14:30:00 UTC\",\r\n        \"timestamp\": \"1494599400\"\r\n      },\r\n\r\nI think the issue is due to the **eventdate.timestap** being a **string** rather than **numeric** value. Is there a way I can change this when being assigned to the **attributeName**. Thank you!",
